titles.title: A concurrent resolution to provide for the counting on January 6, 1993, of the electoral votes for President and Vice President of the United States.

vote.text: Submitted in the Senate, considered, and agreed to without amendment by Voice Vote.

action.text: The previous question was ordered without objection.

vote.text: On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to without objection.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

bill.summary: 1/5/1993--Introduced. Provides for the counting of electoral votes for the President and Vice President on January 6, 1993.
